 Casserly ([[Westmeath]])\n| attendance = 60,072 \n| stack      = yes\n}}\n{{footballbox collapsible \n| date       = 31 August 1997\n| round      = Semi-final \n| team1      = [[Mayo GAA|Mayo]] \n| score      = 0-13 - 0-7 \n| team2      = [[Offaly GAA|Offaly]] \n| goals1     = M Sheridan 0-4, K McDonald 0-3, D Nestor 0-2, F Costello 0-1, L McHale 0-1, K O'Neill 0-1, P Fallon 0-1.\n| goals2     = D Reynolds 0-4, C Quinn 0-1, P Brady 0-1, J Grennan 0-1.\n| stadium    = [[Croke Park]], [[Dublin]]\n| referee    = P Russell ([[County Tipperary|Tipperary]])\n| attendance = 56,369\n| stack      = yes\n}}\n\n'''Final'''\n\n{{footballbox collapsible \n| date       = 28 September 1997\n| round      = Final \n| team1      = [[Kerry GAA|Kerry]] \n| score      = 0-13 - 1-7  \n| team2      = [[Mayo GAA|Mayo]] \n| goals1     = M Fitzgerald 0-9, P Laide 0-2, D \u00d3 S\u00e9 0-1, J Crowley 0-1.\n| goals2     = C McDonald 1-1, M Sheridan 0-3, J Horan 0-2, C McManamon 0-1.\n| stadium    = [[Croke Park]], [[Dublin]]\n| referee    = B White ([[Wexford]])\n| attendance = 65,601\n| stack      = yes\n}}\n\n{{Main article|1997 All-Ireland Senior Football Championship Final}}\n\n==Championship statistics==\n\n===Top scorers===\n\n;Overall\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Rank\n! Player\n! County\n! Tally\n! Total\n! Matches\n! Average\n|-\n|rowspan=1 align=center|1\n|[[Maurice Fitzgerald (footballer)|Maurice Fitzgerald]]\n|[[Kerry GAA|Kerry]]\n|align=center|0-28\n|align=center|28\n|align=center|4\n|align=center|7.00\n|-\n|rowspan=2 align=center|2\n|Maurice Sheridan\n|[[Mayo GAA|Mayo]]\n|align=center|0-27\n|align=center|27\n|align=center|5\n|align=center|5.20\n|-\n|David Reynolds\n|[[Offaly GAA|Offaly]]\n|align=center|0-27\n|align=center|27\n|align=center|5\n|align=center|5.20\n|-\n|rowspan=1 align=center|4\n|[[Declan Darcy]]\n|[[Leitrim GAA|Leitrim]]\n|align=center|2-19\n|align=center|25\n|align=center|2\n|align=center|12.50\n|-\n|rowspan=1 align=center|5\n|[[Trevor Giles]]\n|[[Meath GAA|Mea